#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:417
msgid ""
"This tool will \"reverse\" the direction of any curve with at least one "
"selected element (i.e. the start point will become the end one, and *vice "
"versa*). This is mainly useful when using a curve as path, or using the "
"bevel and taper options."
msgstr ""
"Cet outil va \"inverser\" la direction de toute courbe avec au moins un "
"élément sélectionné (c.à.d. le point de début va devenir le point de fin, et "
"*vice versa*). C'est utile principalement dans l'utilisation d'une courbe "
"comme chemin, ou l'utilisation des options *bevel* et *taper*. "

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:425
msgid "Show/Hide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:427
msgid ""
"When in *Edit Mode*, you can hide and reveal elements from the display. You "
"can only show or hide control points, as segments are always shown, unless "
"all control points of the connected curve are hidden, in which case the "
"curve is fully hidden."
msgstr ""
"En *Mode Édition*, vous pouvez cacher et révéler des éléments affichage. "
"Vous pouvez seulement afficher ou cacher les point de contrôle, étant donné "
"que les segments sont toujours affichés, à moins que tous les points de "
"contrôle de la courbe connectée sont cachés, auquel cas la courbe est "
"complètement cachée."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:432
msgid ""
"See :ref:`object-show-hide` in *Object Mode*. See also the :doc:`/modeling/"
"curves/curve_display` panel."
msgstr ""
"Voir :ref:`object-show-hide` en *Mode Objet*. Voir aussi le panneau :doc:`/"
"modeling/curves/curve_display`."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:439
msgid "Set Spline Type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst
msgid ""
"Panel:    :menuselection:`Tool Shelf --> Tools --> Curve Tools --> Curves: "
"Set Spline type`"
msgstr ""
"Panneau :    :menuselection:`Tool Shelf --> Tools --> Curve Tools --> "
"Curves: Set Spline type`"

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:450
msgid "Set Spline Type button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:452
msgid ""
"You can convert splines in a curve object between Bézier, NURBS, and Poly "
"curves. Press :kbd:`T` to bring up the Tool Shelf. Clicking on the *Set "
"Spline Type* button will allow you to select the Spline type (Poly, Bézier "
"or NURBS)."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez convertir des splines en un objet Courbe entre Bézier, NURBS, et "
"Poly Courbe. Pressez :kbd:`T` pour accéder au Tool Shelf. Le clic sur le "
"bouton *Set Spline Type* vous permettra de sélectionner le type de Spline "
"(Poly, Bézier or NURBS)."

#: ../../manual/modeling/curves/editing/introduction.rst:456
msgid ""
"Note, this is not a \"smart\" conversion, i.e. Blender does not try to keep "
"the same shape, nor the same number of control points. For example, when "
"converting a NURBS to a Bézier, each group of three NURBS control points "
"become a unique Bézier one (center point and two handles)."
msgstr ""
"Notez que ce n'est par une conversion \"intelligente\", càd. que Blender ne "
"cherche ni à garder la même forme, ni le même nombre de points de contrôle. "
"Par exemple, la conversion d'un NURBS en Bézier, chaque groupe de trois "
"points de contrôle NURBS devient un unique point Bézier (un point central et "
"deux poignées)"

